voices, find space, like this, in the world of Old English Studies?" With this in mind we invite a new generation of readers to try their own hand at translating Beowulf in the workbook space provided opposite this community translation. It is often through the effort of translating that we see the reality of the original.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aEpic poetry, English (Old). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBeowulf.  aOld English literature.  acommunity translation.  amedieval poetry.  atranslation methods.1 aAbbott, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbbott, Jean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFafinski, Mateusz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFafinski, Mateusz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTreharne, Elaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTreharne, Elaine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781641894746zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781641894746zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781641894746/original  a978-3-11-074322-7 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZD